 <h1 class="title topictitle1">Annotation and text translation window</h1>

 <div class="body conbody">
  <p class="p">The annotations and text translation window is placed on the right of the BTS user interface.
   You can <a class="xref" href="oberflaeche_funktionen_e5.html">maximize and minimize</a> the window with
    <img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_w3j_gn3_ns" src="Images/icons/extra%20icons/maximize.png"></img> and <img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_qkj_gn3_ns" src="Images/icons/extra%20icons/minimize.png"></img> buttons.</p>

  <p class="p"><u class="ph u">The "Annotations" tab </u> can contain the following elements: </p>

  <p class="p"><img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_p3k_pz3_sr" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/annotation.png"></img> "Annotation"</p>

  <p class="p"><img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_fjn_yz3_sr" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/rubrum.png"></img> "Rubrum"</p>

  <p class="p"><img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_qrx_zz3_sr" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/comment.png"></img> "Comment"</p>

  <p class="p"><img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_mck_31j_sr" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/subtext.png"></img>
   "Glosse"</p>

  
  <p class="p">Click one of them in order to display their content. The related content will be marked in the
   text with different colours: bright red for Rubra; yellow for comments; black for Annotations and
   blue for Glosses. Clicking an annotation will also cause the underlining of the related fragment
   in the text to appear thicker. Additionally, for Annotations, Rubra and Comments, a small bar
   will appear on the right side of the Text-Editor with the corresponding colour. Clicking on the
   bar will bring you to the marked fragment of the text. </p>

  <p class="p">Each annotation, rubrum, comment and gloss contains a toolbar with the following buttons:</p>

  <p class="p"><img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_ult_dv3_sr" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/chain-add.png"></img> "Add Current Text
   Selection as Reference" </p>

  <p class="p"><img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_zwn_fv3_sr" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/chain-edit.png"></img> "Update Current
   Reference"</p>

  <p class="p"><img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_zjx_hv3_sr" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/chain-delete.png"></img> "Remove Current
   Reference" </p>

  <p class="p"><img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_jjk_l5t_mr" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/edit.png"></img> "Edit Comment" or "Edit
   Annotation". This opens a window with different content for annotation, rubrum and comment. It is
   not available for <img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_mb4_q1j_sr" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/subtext.png"></img>
   "Glosse".</p>

  <p class="p">You can use the first three buttons to connect the existing comments, annotations, rubra and
   subtexts/glosses to other parts of the text. </p>

  <p class="p">Clicking on the "Edit Annotation" will display passport editor for annotations and rubra. Each
   annotation will have its own ID and its relation to the chosen text will be shown in the
   "Relations" tab. </p>

  <p class="p">By clicking an "Edit Comment", a "Comment Editor" window will appear. You can enter a title for
   your comment in the upper input field and the content of your comment in the lower input field.
   Below there is also a section where you can see or edit a relation of the comment to the text,
   using the ID.</p>

  <p class="p"><img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_m3d_ry4_sr" src="Images/icons/full/obj16/delete.png"></img> "Delete" will delete
   the currently selected element.</p>

  <p class="p">To learn more about annotations click <a class="xref" href="howto_annotationen.html">here</a>. </p>

  <p class="p"><u class="ph u">"Text translation" tab</u></p>

  <p class="p">"Text translation" tab shows a continuous, sentence by sentence translation and allows for a
   continuous proof reading. The languages <img class="image" id="concept_cpy_xss_mr__image_w1q_vm3_ns" src="Images/icons/full/icon16/locale.png"></img>dropdown menu allows to select translation in the relevant languages.
   Sentences which have not been translated yet are marked as "## no trans: de ##", "## no trans: en
   ##ยง" etc. A leftclick on a sentence activates the same sentence in the "Sign text editor", in the
   "Transliteration" editor as well as in the "Sentence translation" window. A typo or another
   problem observed in the continuous translation can be altered in the "Sentence translation"
   window.</p>

